cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY

This paper is about improving the computational efficiency and memory footprint of deep neural networks by using low precision weights, activations, and gradients. This topic is closely related to machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses a learning scheme for exploring multiple precision configurations, which is a technique used in neural networks (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.AI, followed by cs.NE and cs.SY.
